  text: Your VBA line is doing a comparison, not an assignment of trimmed text.

The problem is here:

```vb
c.Value = ("C2") = Left(ws.Range("C2"), Len(ws.Range("C2")) - 3)
```

`("C2") = Left(...)` is evaluated as a True/False test, so VBA returns `FALSE` for each row, and then assigns that Boolean to `c.Value`.

You also keep referencing `"C2"` every time instead of using the current cell `c`.

A correct VBA version would be:

```vb
Sub RemoveChar()

